content: I've seen some of those, but there are a few I haven't checked out yet. By the way, I've been going to stand-up comedy shows a lot lately - I just saw Alex Stevens at the Laugh Out Loud club on Friday, and it was amazing. I'm actually trying to get into stand-up myself, so I've been attending open mic nights and writing new jokes every day. Do you have any tips on how to structure a comedy set?
